definition.@value: This involves a perforation (hole) in the tympanic membrane and active bacterial infection within the middle ear space for several weeks or more. There may be enough pus that it drains to the outside of the ear (otorrhea), or the purulence may be minimal enough to only be seen on examination using a binocular microscope, unspecified.

longDefinition.@value:
Suppurative otitis media is inflammatory disease of the middle ear with
purulent discharge.
